# Discord Bot Configuration
# Cara mendapatkan token: https://discord.com/developers/applications
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token_here
DISCORD_CHANNEL_ID=your_discord_channel_id_here

# Telegram Bot Configuration  
# Cara mendapatkan token: Chat dengan @BotFather di Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_telegram_chat_id_here

# Supabase Configuration (REQUIRED for public sharing)
# Get these from Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual tokens
# 3. NEVER commit .env file to git (it's in .gitignore)

# Discord Setup:
# 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Create new application
# 3. Go to Bot section, create bot
# 4. Copy token to DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN
# 5. Invite bot to your server with "Send Messages" and "Attach Files" permissions
# 6. Get channel ID by right-clicking channel and "Copy ID" (enable Developer Mode first)

# Telegram Setup:
# 1. Chat with @BotFather on Telegram
# 2. Send /newbot and follow instructions
# 3. Copy token to TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
# 4. Get your chat ID by messaging @userinfobot or create a group and add the bot
# 5. For group: Get group chat ID (negative number)

# Supabase Setup (REQUIRED for sharing):
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and create account
# 2. Create new project
# 3. Go to Settings > API
# 4. Copy "Project URL" to SUPABASE_URL
# 5. Copy "anon public" key to SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 6. Add both to your Vercel environment variables
# 
# Database tables will be created automatically on first use
# No additional setup required!